---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const lastUpdated = "June 23, 2025";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms & Conditions"
  description="Terms and conditions for using calpercentage.com. Free to use, no account required. Calculation results are for informational purposes only. Read our full terms of service."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 py-16 sm:py-24">

    <p class="form-label mb-4">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold text-ink mb-4" style="letter-spacing:-0.05em; line-height:1.1;">
      Terms &amp; Conditions
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-12">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-line); padding-top:3rem;" class="space-y-10">

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Introduction</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          Welcome to calpercentage.com. These Terms and Conditions ("Terms") explain the rules for using this website, including all calculators, tools, and blog posts.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          Please read these Terms before using the site. By using calpercentage.com, you agree to follow these rules and our <a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-ink underline">Privacy Policy</a>. If you disagree with any part, please stop using the site.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Definitions</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">Here's what some words in this document mean:</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong class="text-ink">"Site"</strong> means calpercentage.com and everything on it.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">"User," "you," or "your"</strong> means anyone who visits or uses the site.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">"We," "us," or "our"</strong> means calpercentage.com and the people who run it.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">"Content"</strong> means everything on the site — text, calculators, articles, and more.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">"Services"</strong> means the percentage calculators and tools on the site.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">"Results"</strong> means the numbers the calculators give you.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Acceptance of terms</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          By visiting or using calpercentage.com, you confirm that you are at least 13 years old (or 16 in some countries) and that you agree to follow these Terms.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          If you use the site for a company or organization, you confirm you have permission to agree to these Terms on their behalf.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          If we update these Terms, continuing to use the site means you accept the new version. Check this page occasionally for any changes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Description of the service</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          calpercentage.com offers free online percentage calculators for everyday use, learning, and personal math. The tools include:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><a href="/percentage-calculator" class="text-ink underline">Percentage Calculator</a> — find P% of a value, what percentage X is of Y, or recover a base value when you know the percentage and the result.</li>
          <li><a href="/percentage-of-number" class="text-ink underline">Percentage of Number Calculator</a> — determine what percentage one number represents of another.</li>
          <li><a href="/percentage-increase" class="text-ink underline">Percentage Increase / Decrease Calculator</a> — calculate the percentage change between two values, or find the new value after applying a percentage shift.</li>
          <li><a href="/discount-calculator" class="text-ink underline">Discount Calculator</a> — find the final price after single or stacked discounts, or reverse-calculate the original price from a sale price.</li>
          <li><a href="/tip-calculator" class="text-ink underline">Tip Calculator</a> — calculate tip amounts, total bills, and per-person splits for restaurant checks.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mt-3">
          All calculations happen in your browser — nothing is sent to a server. The site is completely free: no sign-up, no subscription, no login. We may add or remove features at any time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Permitted and prohibited use</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          You're welcome to use calpercentage.com for free, personal use — like homework, everyday math, or sharing links with friends.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">You may <strong class="text-ink">not</strong>:</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Use the site for anything illegal.</li>
          <li>Try to break or slow down the site.</li>
          <li>Use bots or automated tools to copy large amounts of content.</li>
          <li>Copy or sell any part of the site — its design, code, or articles — without our permission.</li>
          <li>Upload viruses or harmful software.</li>
          <li>Try to hack into the site or its systems.</li>
          <li>Present the site's results as official figures from a government, bank, doctor, or school.</li>
          <li>Embed the site inside another website or app without our permission.</li>
          <li>Do anything that could harm the site or its users.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mt-3">
          If you break these rules, we may block your access and report it to the authorities.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Accuracy and reliability of calculations</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          Our calculators use standard math formulas and are designed to give you accurate results. We fix any errors we find quickly.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          However, the results are <strong class="text-ink">for information and learning only</strong>. They should not replace advice from a professional for important decisions.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">In particular:</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Talk to a financial advisor or accountant before making big money decisions.</li>
          <li>Check your school grades against your school's official records.</li>
          <li>Use proper payroll software for business pay calculations.</li>
          <li>Check any health-related percentages with a doctor.</li>
          <li>Confirm legal or contract percentages with a lawyer.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mt-3">
          We do not guarantee that results are always perfect. You are responsible for how you use them.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Intellectual property</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          Everything on calpercentage.com — the design, articles, code, and calculators — belongs to us and is protected by copyright law.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          You are allowed to use the site for your own personal, non-commercial use. You may <strong class="text-ink">not</strong>:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Copy or download the code or content to sell or share.</li>
          <li>Modify or create new products based on our work.</li>
          <li>Sell or rent access to any part of the site.</li>
          <li>Remove our copyright notices.</li>
          <li>Copy large sections of our articles onto other sites without permission.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mt-3">
          Note: the math formulas themselves (like "percentage change = ((new − old) / old) × 100") are not copyrighted — they're just math. But our explanations, design, and how we present them are our own creative work.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mt-3">
          You're welcome to quote or reference our content with a link back to us. For anything else, please ask us first.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          calpercentage.com is offered "as is" — meaning we provide it as-is, without any promises or guarantees. We do not guarantee:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>That the site will always be fast, secure, or error-free.</li>
          <li>That the site or its results will meet your specific needs.</li>
          <li>That the site is free from viruses or bugs.</li>
          <li>That results are always 100% accurate or complete.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mt-3">
          Some countries' laws may still give you additional rights even when a site says this.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          As far as the law allows, we are not responsible for any losses or problems caused by using this site. This includes:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Lost money, business, or earnings.</li>
          <li>Losses from trusting the calculator results.</li>
          <li>Lost or damaged data.</li>
          <li>Damage to your reputation or savings.</li>
          <li>Errors in the site's content or calculator results.</li>
          <li>Unauthorized access to our servers.</li>
          <li>Viruses sent through the site by someone else.</li>
          <li>The site going offline or shutting down.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mt-3">
          This applies no matter the reason — even if we were told something might go wrong.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Indemnification</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          If your use of the site breaks these Terms and causes a legal problem for us (including legal costs), you agree to cover those costs. This includes misusing results or violating someone else's rights.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">External links</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          Our site may link to other websites. These links are just for convenience — we don't own or control those sites and are not responsible for what's on them. Visiting any linked site is your own choice and subject to that site's own rules.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Service availability</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          We try to keep calpercentage.com online all the time, but we can't guarantee it will always be available. The site might go down for maintenance, technical issues, or reasons out of our control. We may change or shut down the site at any time without warning.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Accessibility</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          We work to make calpercentage.com easy to use for everyone, including people with disabilities. We aim to follow the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA — for example, making the site work with keyboards and screen readers. If you find anything hard to use, please let us know.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          We may update these Terms at any time. When we do, we'll update the date at the top of this page. If you keep using the site after changes are posted, you accept the new Terms. If you disagree, please stop using the site.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Governing law and dispute resolution</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          These Terms follow the law. If you're in a place where using this site is not allowed, please don't use it.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-3">
          If there's ever a disagreement about these Terms or how you used the site, we ask that you contact us first to sort it out. If we can't resolve it within 30 days, either side can take it to the appropriate legal process.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          These Terms don't take away any rights you already have under your country's consumer or data protection laws.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Entire agreement</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          These Terms and our <a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-ink underline">Privacy Policy</a> together are the full agreement between you and calpercentage.com about how you use the site. They replace any earlier agreements we may have had.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-6 mb-4">
          If you have questions about these Terms, spotted a problem, or need help understanding anything, please reach out via our contact page. We aim to reply within 5 business days.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-secondary">Contact us</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
